        "executive_summary": "MOASD delivered a composite performance score of 54 out of 100 (where 50 represents the network average), positioning the clinic modestly above the midpoint. The clinic showed meaningful progress on patient flow, with average delay improving to 5.5 minutes in March from 6.0 minutes in February\u2014a measurable 8.8% reduction that sits well below the company average of 7.06 minutes. However, one metric warrants attention: treatments running past closing time rose from 0.2 per day in February to 0.5 per day in March, a 181.2% increase that suggests emerging scheduling pressure despite solid compliance.",
        "highlights": [
          "MOASD's scheduler compliance reached 81.4% in March, extending a three-month improvement trend (R\u00b2 = 0.91) and reflecting disciplined adherence to iOptimize recommendations relative to a baseline three-month average of 65.7%. Patient wait times have become a genuine strength for the clinic\u2014the 5.5-minute average delay in March represents best-in-class performance when benchmarked against the company average of 7.06 minutes, with the clinic achieving this while maintaining full iAssign utilization at 100.0%."
