          "The biggest performance opportunity sits with La Jolla, where chair utilization stands at 42.9%\u201433% below the company average of 64.13%\u2014indicating substantial untapped capacity. We recommend reviewing La Jolla's scheduling templates in tandem with their iOptimize recommendations to identify whether template design, patient mix, or session duration assumptions are inadvertently creating gaps; this would be a concrete starting point to unlock chair flow efficiency and close the utilization gap collaboratively with the clinic leadership."
